DOC.TE:
   It's not all darkness and droogs at the playhouse this week;
Playbox is also serving younger audiences on Friday afternoon with
poet Ted Hughes' quirky version of "Beauty and the Beast."

   No decision on an L.A. Super Bowl will be made at this meeting;
the earliest such a vote would take place would be at the league
meetings in March.

   Nine times in as many months, Los Angeles county officials asked
for unfettered access to the EIDC's financial records. Nine times,
the EIDC refused, arguing that some of its data are proprietary.
